# Testes de Widgets Flutter

## Teste Basico com testWidgets

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_test/flutter_test.dart';
import 'package:my_app/widgets/app_button.dart';

void main() {
  testWidgets('AppButton renderiza com label correto', (tester) async {
    await tester.pumpWidget(
      const MaterialApp(home: Scaffold(body: AppButton(label: 'Salvar', onPressed: _noop))),
    );
    expect(find.text('Salvar'), findsOneWidget);
  });

  testWidgets('AppButton chama onPressed ao tocar', (tester) async {
    var pressed = false;
    await tester.pumpWidget(
      MaterialApp(home: Scaffold(body: AppButton(label: 'OK', onPressed: () => pressed = true))),
    );
    await tester.tap(find.text('OK'));
    expect(pressed, isTrue);
  });
}

void _noop() {}
```

## Finders

```dart
find.text('Salvar');
find.byType(ElevatedButton);
find.byKey(const Key('submit-btn'));
find.byIcon(Icons.add);
find.byWidgetPredicate((w) => w is Text && w.data == 'Salvar');
```

## Interacoes

```dart
await tester.tap(find.byType(ElevatedButton));
await tester.enterText(find.byType(TextField), 'texto');
await tester.drag(find.byType(ListView), const Offset(0, -300));
await tester.longPress(find.byType(ListTile));
await tester.pump();           // proximo frame
await tester.pumpAndSettle();  // aguarda animacoes
```

## Teste com Estado Assincrono

```dart
testWidgets('carrega e exibe dados', (tester) async {
  await tester.pumpWidget(const MaterialApp(home: UserProfile(id: '1')));
  expect(find.byType(CircularProgressIndicator), findsOneWidget);
  await tester.pumpAndSettle();
  expect(find.text('Joao Silva'), findsOneWidget);
});
```

## Convencoes

- Sempre envolver widgets em `MaterialApp` no teste
- `pumpAndSettle` para animacoes, `pump` para frame unico
- Preferir `find.text` e `find.byType` sobre `find.byKey`
- Testar estados: inicial, loading, sucesso, erro
- Um `testWidgets` por comportamento
